The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Bidappa freed on wife plea

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Bangalore, July 15: Fashion guru and choreographer Prasad Bidappa will return home shortly.

 He was allowed to walk free by a Dubai court after 33 days in detention for carrying two grams of marijuana in his hand baggage. 

 The release order came on a mercy petition submitted by his wife and theatre personality Judith Bidappa.

 His friends in the fashion circuit were told of his release by business contacts in Dubai. 

 Its excellent news and we are all relieved that Prasads ordeal has ended. We are waiting for him to come back, designer Manoviraj Khosla said.

 Bidappas friends hinted that he would land here in a day or two.

 His family or colleagues at Prasad Bidappa Associates were not available for comments.

 The office of the Indian consul-general in Dubai, however, could not confirm whether the charges against Bidappa were dropped.

 On July 13, a court hearing the case adjourned the proceedings to July 27.

 The fashion guru was arrested at Dubai International Airport on June 11. 

 Bidappa went to Dubai to attend a fashion meet and a childrens programme.




